==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Boat bug
<hw>Boat" bug`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An aquatic
hemipterous insect of the genus <gen>Notonecta</gen>; -- so called from
swimming on its back, which gives it the appearance of a little boat.
Called also <altname>boat fly</altname>, <altname>boat insect</altname>,
<altname>boatman</altname>, and <altname>water
boatman</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Boatful</ent>⟦br⟧
